<br>
Now place military personnel or equipment inside one of the above.  It is no longer a civilian site, it is a legit military target.<br>
<br>
Vice versa.  If you take thousands of civilians and place them in a chemical or weapons storage area, it is STILL a military target.<br>
<br>
Regretful as it might be, remember, most of the enemies of the United States don't play by any of the rules at all.  Yes, we break some, intentionally and accidentally, but we still play along the lines of right.  Putting civilians in a site in an attempt to prevent us from bombing it will not, never has and never will, work.  We are going to go to war to win, and protect as many of our troops lives as possible.  Skipping a site because Saddam placed civilians inside will NOT be protecting our troops or give us a victory.<br>
